.TH SUM "1" "April 2026" "GNU coreutils 9.11" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
sum \- checksum and count the blocks in a file
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sum
[\fI\,OPTION\/\fR]... [\fI\,FILE\/\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.\" Add any additional description here
.PP
Print or check BSD (16\-bit) checksums.
Legacy interface to the cksum utility.
.PP
With no FILE, or when FILE is \-, read standard input.
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#sum-r'\fB\-r\fP\X'tty: link'
use BSD sum algorithm (the default), use 1K blocks
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#sum-s'\fB\-s, \-\-sysv\fP\X'tty: link'
use System V sum algorithm, use 512 bytes blocks
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/sum#sum--help'\fB\-\-help\fP\X'tty: link'
display this help and exit
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/sum#sum--version'\fB\-\-version\fP\X'tty: link'
output version information and exit
